72 years (range, 18-95 years). The median TTP was 13.6 h (range,
3.6-95.2 h). Attributable mortality rate (27.5%) was not related to
the TTP (P=0.558) nor to the comorbidities. Age >60 years was the only
independent predictor of attributable mortality (P 11.3 h had a
negative predictive value of 96.4% for endocarditis. TTP was not
related to methicillin susceptibility nor resistance of Staphylococcus
aureus (P=0.934).

Conclusion: In our elderly population, shorter TTP was significantly
associated with a central source of infection and a persistent SAB. In
addition for the first time, community-acquired SAB was associated
with a shorter TTP. TTP  may contribute to a better management of SAB
by facilitating clinical decisions, especially in endocarditis
