AB  - Abstract This study evaluated the determinants of mortality and the T
cell immune response in patients with persistent Staphylococcus aureus
bacteremia (SAB). This was a prospective cohort study and patients
with confirmed SAB were enrolled from 2008 to 2020. We compared
clinical, microbiological, and genotypic features between surviving
and deceased patients with persistent SAB. The concentrations of
cytokines and the proportions of IFN-γ secreting CD4 + T cells were
